cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper discusses fine-tuning of deep networks for image retrieval and fine-grained classification tasks, which are typically associated with computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The proposed algorithm involves layer-wise pruning and auto-tuning of learning rates, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the experiments involve image datasets, which are also relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
